      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must be documented and traceable to the computational boundary conditions at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump hemolysis experiments were conducted at five flow-speed combinations (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Inlet/outlet pressures, fluid temperature, and hematocrit were recorded and directly mapped to CFD boundary conditions. Full traceability documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) must agree with experimental values within combined uncertainty bounds at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Predicted RH values ranged 0.71–0.94 versus experimental 0.68–0.97 across all five operating points. All predictions fell within ±15% of experimental means, within combined experimental and model uncertainty. Acceptance criterion RH < 1 met at all points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
