      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative hemolysis index) must be directly linked to the clinical decision endpoint at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the regulatory-accepted surrogate for pump-induced hemolysis used in 510(k) submissions. It directly quantifies red blood cell damage relative to a predicate device, making it fully relevant to the worst-case operating condition identification objective."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
